<TITLE> Eight arrested with illicit gold trade in Old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 5 (bdnews24.com)The Rapid Action Battalion arrested eight people with alleged ties to illicit gold trade in a raid on five jewellery shops in Tantibazar of Old Dhaka Wednesday. A RAB-10 officer, Humayun Kabir, who led the raid, told bdnews24.com that the elite force had also seized 660 bhoris (1 bhori=11.66 grams) of gold ornaments, acting on a tip-off. Kabir alleged that the shops had been engaged in buying stolen gold ornaments and reselling them after moulding. Four of the fiver shops are: KC Bullion Store, Harun Bullion, Ma Gold House and Tanmay Bullion Store. The fifth shop was not immediately named by the RAB. The gold traders failed to produce invoices against the seized ornaments as a proof of legal purchase, Kabir said. The RAB arrested Dulal Ghosh, Harunur Rashid, Nazrul Islam, Narayan Ghosh, Alok Das, Suranjit Sur, Sukumar Nandi and Sagar Ghosh. bd
